    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>SMOKING BAN</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Karen Demasters</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Superior Court Judge Linda Feinberg overturns no-smoking ordinance that bans smoking indoors in Princeton Township and Princeton Borough, NJ (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A Superior Court judge last week overturned a no-smoking ordinance that essentially banned smoking indoors in Princeton Township and Princeton Borough, ruling that the restriction went beyond what municipal officials are allowed to do.</p>
        <p>The Princeton Regional Health Commission enacted New Jersey's toughest smoking ban in June, but did not enforce it after a challenge was filed. The ban would have applied to all indoor areas except homes, private vehicles and cigar shops.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>A Superior Court judge last week overturned a no-smoking ordinance that essentially banned smoking indoors in Princeton Township and Princeton Borough, ruling that the restriction went beyond what municipal officials are allowed to do.</p>
        <p>The Princeton Regional Health Commission enacted New Jersey's toughest smoking ban in June, but did not enforce it after a challenge was filed. The ban would have applied to all indoor areas except homes, private vehicles and cigar shops.</p>
        <p>A municipality cannot enact smoking regulations that are stricter than those enacted by the state, said Judge Linda Feinberg of Superior Court in Trenton.</p>
        <p>Karen DeMasters</p>
        <p>BRIEFING: THE LAW</p>
      </block>
